  },
  {
    question: "How often are these guides updated?",
    answer: "All guides are reviewed and updated quarterly to ensure they reflect the latest Swiss insurance regulations, premium trends, and provider offerings. This is especially important before the annual switching period (September-November)."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I trust the information in these guides?",
    answer: "Yes, all information is verified by licensed Swiss insurance experts with years of experience in the field. We maintain strict editorial standards and do not allow insurance companies to influence our content or recommendations."
  },
  {
    question: "I'm not an expat. Are these guides still relevant for me?",
    answer: "Absolutely! While we specialize in helping expats navigate the Swiss insurance system, the information and strategies in our guides are equally applicable to Swiss nationals and long-term residents looking to optimize their insurance coverage."
  },
  {
    question: "What if I need personalized advice beyond these guides?",
    answer: "If your situation requires more personalized guidance, we offer free consultations with our insurance experts who can provide tailored advice specific to your unique circumstances. Simply use the consultation button found on each guide."
